what are semantic tags ? and how they help in seo?

Semantic HTML tags improve SEO (Search Engine Optimization) by providing meaningful structure to web pages, it easier for search engines to crawl, understand, and rank content.

1. Better Content Understanding

Search engines analyze the structure of a webpage to understand its content.
Semantic tags like <article>, <section>, <header>, and <footer> clearly define different parts of a page, making it easier for crawlers to index relevant content.

2. Improved Readability for Search Engines

Using <h1> - <h6> tags properly helps Google and other search engines determine the main topics of a page.
<nav> identifies navigation links, making site indexing more efficient.

3. Enhanced Accessibility
Semantic tags improve accessibility for screen readers used by visually impaired users.
Search engines prioritize user-friendly experiences, which positively affects rankings.

<header>
  <h1>SEO Best Practices</h1>
  <nav>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#importance">Importance</a></li>
      <li><a href="#benefits">Benefits</a></li>
    </ul>
  </nav>
</header>

<article>
  <section id="importance">
    <h2>Why SEO Matters?</h2>
    <p>SEO improves visibility and drives traffic...</p>
  </section>
  
  <section id="benefits">
    <h2>Key Benefits of SEO</h2>
    <p>Better rankings, higher engagement...</p>
  </section>
</article>

<footer>
  <p>&copy; 2025 SEO Experts</p>
</footer>

Using semantic tags helps search engines understand, index, and rank your page better, improving SEO and overall site performance.
